column5: Heya buddy.  Let me be the first to welcome you aboard to our board. hehe  You will love the guys here.  We are all a big family and we are glad you are now part of it.  Get posting as we look forward to your insight.  my 2 cents  2many
Welcome aboard!
Welcome aboard and do not listen to DouG

Howdy Folks!  First time poster, long time lurker......  Well, I've visited numerous boards and found this one to be the most entertaining.  I guess a little about myself: Grew up in Thunder Bay, 21 years, sparked my interest for the outdoors. Currently living in Ottawa, have a cottage on White Lake, love fishing for Large Mouth Bass with my Lovley Wife and Son.  Looking forward to posting outings soon.  Stay Safe!
welcome aboard
New kids arent allowed in our club, bounce!   Kidding, welcome aboard!
Welcome to the board... its definately the best one on the net...Hope you enjoy
Welcome aboard.  Lookin' forward to the reports.
Welcome, we'll be waiting for the reports, don't forget the pics.
Welcome to the zoo...enjoy your stay  Maureen
Eee doggies, young feller..take yer shoes off an stay awhile!
Hey there!  Since you've been a long time lurker, then you know that this is the BEST board around.  Hope to see many reports and pics from you in the near future.  Welcome aboard!
<EMBED src="http://www.ontariofishing.net/welcome.mp3" autostart=true hidden=true>  Welcome in...
Welcome
Welcoame to the fishing Zoo!!!!!!!!  MTP
I'll tell ya's all now, us Thunderbayites, or former ones, are takin over this board, lol  And there ain't nuttin you can do about it.  Welcome aboard Mikcol. Tis a great place to be.
Another Ottawa resident, Do you get much fishing in here? Or mostly at the cottage?
A big welcome to Mikcol, and thanks for a very gracious introduction.  Make yourself at home.  Now, shut the door, replace the beer in the fridge and fill the ice trays, fer dog's sake already.
Welcome, You're the first to have music on your link!!   dsn
welcome
Welcome!  Great people on this board with some good insight.  Enjoy your stay!
Welcome to our OFC community Mikcol. Enjoy the ride.
Welcome, it is a great place here with tons of info.  But if we catch you singing "Hangin tough" you will be asked to leave  :lol:

Thanks for the warm welcome folks!  I dig the music!  Crusty, I fished the usual suspects around the area, but mostly spend my time at the cottage these days.  No worries Verno, my head does look something like a sewing machine but trust me, I'm no Singer!

Hey welcome, Hope all is well..... When you say white lake are you talking north of kingston? I have a cottage on greater bobs lake (bucks bay) And so far that's the best fishing for me. Frontenac county. Well have a good one and enjoy lots of real nice people here.
Hi Bookoobeast,  No, we're just outside of Arnprior.  I know of the White Lake your talking about though.
Welcome aboard! This is a great site with alot of great people.  You will have a blast here!
